      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the smoke machine reveals a leak in the intake manifold gasket, it could certainly be the source of your P0171 code. A leak in the manifold gasket would allow unmetered air to enter the combustion chamber, leading to a lean air-fuel mixture. This is not a minor issue; it's quite significant because it directly affects the engine's performance and can cause misfires, rough idling, and even damage to the catalytic converter over time. So, if the smoke machine detects a leak in the intake manifold gasket, it's a major headache worth addressing. Repairing the leak will likely resolve the P0171 code and improve your Camry's overall performance.",
